	<WorldObjectDef>
		<defName>SWCPArmyForce_ZsinjDominion_Raptors</defName>
		<label>Raptor Platoon</label>
		<description>A deployed platoon of Raptors, Warlord Zsinj's elite shock troopers.\n\nThis gathering of armed forces is fully self-sufficient and requires no input from the player to support itself. This unit has its own supply officers and recruiters capable of keeping its supplies stocked and its number of battle-ready soldiers high. It can send forth a full deployment of NPC troops to assist you in battle every 10 days, and can also contribute small reinforcement squads and strike teams for your direct control every 1-3 days.\n\nTrained with intent to be an infantry force superior to even the Imperial Stormtroopers, the Raptors are Warlord Zsinj's elite shock troop unit spearheading his campaign to conquer the Empire. Raptors are designed to instill a new kind of terror in their enemies and subjugates in ways that the Stormtroopers can't match. Not only are Raptors brainwashed for absolute loyalty to Zsinj, they are conditioned for extreme aggression and encouraged to commit brutal atrocities on enemies and civilian populaces loyal to the enemy. Tactically, they are trained to be just as capable in close-quarters melee combat as they are in ranged combat. The shorter-range E-11 carbine used by most Imperial forces has been replaced by the ZK-43 rifle, a longer-range burst-fire weapon that possesses an affixed vibro-bayonet that has proven exceptionally lethal when utilized in unexpected charging maneuvers to enter melee range. Raptor squads are also equipped with heavy anti-armor missile launchers, long-range repeating blasters, and flamethrowers for strategic area-denial tactics (as well as general acts of intimidation). The body armor of the Raptors is closely based on the standard Stormtrooper medium armor, so while exceptionally resistant to blaster fire, Raptors are left vulnerable to enemies with kinetic-based weapons like slugthrowers. Much like the Stormtroopers, Raptors are an excellent general-purpose unit, though Raptors in particular excel in infantry suppression duties.</description>
		
		<texture>UI/WorldMapForceIcons_Armies/RotatedForSomeAnnoyingReason/WMFIcon_Raptor</texture><!--  for some dumbass reason the game rotates this texture 90 degrees clockwise -->
		<expandingIconTexture>UI/WorldMapForceIcons_Armies/WMFIcon_Raptor</expandingIconTexture>
		<fullyExpandedInSpace>true</fullyExpandedInSpace>
		<expandingIcon>true</expandingIcon>
		<expandingIconPriority>10</expandingIconPriority>
		<expandMore>true</expandMore>
		<useDynamicDrawer>true</useDynamicDrawer>
		<rotateGraphicWhenTraveling>false</rotateGraphicWhenTraveling>
		
		<worldObjectClass>ForcesMod.WorldObject_Force</worldObjectClass>
		<nameMaker>SWCPNameMaker_WorldMapForce_RaptorPlatoon_ZsinjDominion</nameMaker>
		
		<modExtensions>
			<li Class="ForcesMod.ForceAbilitiesModExtension">
				<abilityRange>8</abilityRange>
				<forceNameString>SWCPWorldMapForceNameString_RaptorPlatoon</forceNameString>
				<movementSpeedPerDay>24</movementSpeedPerDay>
				<abilities>
					<li>SWCPWMFAbility_ZsinjDominion_SummonNPCRaid_Raptors_full</li>
					<li>SWCPWMFAbility_ZsinjDominion_SummonPlayerUnits_Raptors_small</li>
					<li>SWCPWMFAbility_ZsinjDominion_SummonPlayerUnits_Raptors_big</li>
					
					<li>SWCPWMFAbility_ArtilleryBombardment_antiVehicle</li>
					<li>SWCPWMFAbility_DestroySettlement</li>
				</abilities>
			</li>
		</modExtensions>
	</WorldObjectDef>
	
	
	
	
	
	
	<ForcesMod.ForceAbilityDef>
		<defName>SWCPWMFAbility_ZsinjDominion_SummonNPCRaid_Raptors_full</defName>
		<label>deploy full platoon (NPC)</label>
		<description>Deploy the full platoon as friendly NPCs.</description>
		<workerClass>ForcesMod.ForceAbilityWorker_SpawnRaid</workerClass>
		
		<iconPath>UI/WorldMapForceIcons_Deployments/ZsinjDominion_Raptor_NPC</iconPath>
		<requiresTarget>true</requiresTarget>
		
		<!-- 600,000 = 10 in-game days -->
		<cooldownTicks>600000</cooldownTicks>
		
		<faction>guy762_SWWarlordsFaction_ZsinjDominion</faction>
		<relevantPawnKinds>
			<xSWZsinj_Raptor_24x>24</xSWZsinj_Raptor_24x>
			<xSWZsinj_RaptorRepeater_4x>4</xSWZsinj_RaptorRepeater_4x>
			<xSWZsinj_RaptorFlamethrower_2x>2</xSWZsinj_RaptorFlamethrower_2x>
			<xSWZsinj_RaptorMissile_8x>8</xSWZsinj_RaptorMissile_8x>
			<xSWZsinj_RaptorOfficer_2x>2</xSWZsinj_RaptorOfficer_2x>
		</relevantPawnKinds>
	</ForcesMod.ForceAbilityDef>
	
